[3] Saudi Arabia
Date: Sun 20 Dec 2009
Source: Saudi Gazette [summarized, edited]
<http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2009121657169>


Health Affairs in Jeddah has said that 10 cases of dengue fever have
been registered since floods hit the city's east. "Eight cases have
been recorded since the beginning of this week," said Health Affairs
Director Sami Badawood. "All are in a stable condition."

Jeddah Governor Prince Misha'l Bin Majed held an emergency meeting
Tuesday [15 Dec 2009] of the recently formed Public Health Committee,
headed by Badawood and consisting of representatives from 6 bodies
including King Abdulaziz University, the Red Crescent, Presidency of
Meteorology and Environmental Protection, and other government
bodies. The committee was set up to address any health concerns
resulting from the floods.

--
