[6] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Sun 20 Dec 2009
Source: UAI [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.uai.com.br/htmls/app/noticia173/2009/12/18/noticia_minas,i=140687/DENGUE+POE+22+CIDADES+MINEIRAS+EM+ALERTA.shtml>


According to latest data from the state Secretariat of Health (SES),
up to October this year [2009], Minas Gerais recorded 75 556 cases of
the disease, a decrease of 2.6 percent over the same period last year
[2008], when there were 76 552 [dengue] infected persons. Considering
all Brazil, according to the Minister, the drop was 46 percent in the
number of cases in comparison with 2008. "I do not see this reduction
as negative for the state. In analyzing the situation of Minas
Gerais, we see that the disease is concentrated in about 20
municipalities in a total of 853," said the state Secretary for
Health, Marcos Pestana.

SES data show that in 2006, 714 people were infected by the mosquito
[-borne virus] in Governador Valadares. In just 3 years, the number
increased 9 times, rising to 6290 cases. For the Superintendent of
Epidemiology of SES, Francisco Lemos, the fact that dengue occurs
periodically and hits, often, the same cities does not permit one to
say that there has been negligence or flaws in public policy in these
municipalities, especially in the Vale do Arco. "The year 2009 was
characterized by increased rainfall across the state," he said.

Belo Horizonte, which this year [2009] stepped up actions to combat
the vector, recorded, according to recent data from the Municipal
Secretariat of Health, 22 755 reports of the disease. Of this total,
12 603 cases were confirmed. The north region still has the highest
number of cases, 6036 confirmed, followed by the regions of Venda
Nova, 1410, and northeast with 1379. "The fight must not stop,"
stated the state Secretary of Health, Marcelo Teixeira.

An outbreak of dengue is worrying the authorities of Carangola in the
Zona Mata [forest area], 359 km from Belo Horizonte. In recent days,
the municipal Secretariat of Health reported at least 40 cases, of
which 7 have been confirmed in a laboratory accredited by the SUS.
The recorded [cases] are concentrated in the Bairro do Triangulo, the
most populous of the municipality, where entire families have
contracted the virus. The municipal Secretary of Health, Amaury
Costa, met with representatives of Regional Health Management (GRS)
of Manhumirim to try to draw up a strategy for confronting [the
disease]. To combat the disease, a health barrier will be placed in
the most critical region. In addition to 22 full-time employees of
the National Health Foundation (FUNASA), another 12 will be hired on
an emergency basis for application of insecticide by means of
backpack sprayers.

The [current] situation:

Cities at risk of an outbreak: Governador Valadares, Ipatinga

On alert: Belo Horizonte, Araguari, Betim, Contagem, Coronel
Fabriciano, Divinopolis, Ibirite, Itabira, Juiz de Fora, Monte
Carlos, Pedro Leopoldo, Ribeirao das Neves, Sabara, Santa Luzia, Sete
Lagoas, Teofilo Otoni, Timoteo, Uberaba, Uberlandia, Vespasiano

Stable situation: Conselheiro Lafaiete, Patos de Minas

--
